      <description>&lt;p&gt;I decided to record some screencasts to show how easy it is to deploy &lt;a href=&#34;https://gluster.org/&#34;&gt;GlusterFS&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a title=&#34;Automatically deploying GlusterFS with Puppet-Gluster + Vagrant!&#34; href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2014/01/08/automatically-deploying-glusterfs-with-puppet-gluster-vagrant/&#34;&gt;Puppet-Gluster+Vagrant&lt;/a&gt;. You can follow along even if you don&amp;rsquo;t know anything about Puppet or Vagrant. The hardest part of this process was producing the actual videos!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If recommend first reading my earlier articles if you&amp;rsquo;re planning on following along:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/12/09/vagrant-on-fedora-with-libvirt/&#34;&gt;Vagrant on Fedora with libvirt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2013/12/21/vagrant-vsftp-and-other-tricks/&#34;&gt;Vagrant vsftp and other tricks&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2014/01/02/vagrant-clustered-ssh-and-screen/&#34;&gt;Vagrant clustered SSH and &#39;screen&#39;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2014/01/08/automatically-deploying-glusterfs-with-puppet-gluster-vagrant/&#34;&gt;Automatically deploying GlusterFS with Puppet-Gluster + Vagrant!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;Without any further delay, here are the screencasts:&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 1:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/alt/purpleidea/screencasts/puppet-gluster-screencast.part1.ogv&#34;&gt;Intro, and provisioning of the Puppet server.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
